meta.description:
This course supports you and your team (small and growing tech start-ups) with finding out which funding instruments and investors are a good fit for your business case.
Who is this course for?
It is for young professionals as well as current and aspiring entrepreneurs
What will you learn? 
You will learn
·       how to approach investors timely and effectively for funding;
·       how to identify the types of funding instruments and investors that are suitable for their business context;
·       how to outline the essentials that a successful startup should cover before approaching potential investors;
·       how to describe the principles and practices for pitching their businesses effectively to potential investors.
